      <symbol code="709" id="162" name="Out-of-bounds area &lt;span style=&quot;color:magenta&quot;&gt;(forbidden to cross)&lt;/span&gt;" type="4">
        <description>Out of bounds areas are mapped with the symbol area with forbidden access (528.1). This symbol shall only be used for last minute updates to the competition map (e.g. for areas that may be dangerous for the competitors during the competition, or very late changes to the competition terrain).
An out-of-bounds area is shown with vertical stripes. A bounding line may be drawn if there is no natural boundary, as follows:
- a solid line indicates that the boundary is marked continuously (tapes, etc.) on the ground,
- a dashed line indicates intermittent marking on the ground,
- no line indicates no marking on the ground.

&lt;span style="color:magenta"&gt;It is forbidden to cross an out-of-bounds area!
Competitors violating this rule will be disqualified.&lt;/span&gt;</description>
